        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:28PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
White Plains, or near Dobson, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Airy...
Fairview...
Dobson...
Pilot Mountain...
Bottom...
Level Cross...
and White Plains.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
